icily","Ampolo, Erdas, 2019, Inscriptiones Segestanae. Le iscrizioni greche e latine di Segesta",[262,262,263,264,265,266,267,268,269],"R46KDTZX","77P5MNIR","WHBJDH75","U7GGTWQM","4FSSHE62","Z54HF9PD","X5ZZ4GPT","3PK3JKXR",[271,272,273,27,32,36,274,274,275,276,274,277,278,137],"isic002737","honorific for lucius iulius agrippa, euergetes",{"_":5},"segesta","sicilia","sicily","parco archeologico di segesta","latin",[],{"title":281,"body":282,"divs":283,"editions":308,"images":318,"handnote":319},"ISic002737. Honorific for Lucius Iulius Agrippa, euergetes","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>L(ucio) · Iulio · C(aii) · f(ilio) · Agrippae \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>euergetae · \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>hic · plateam · a · Sosi\u003Cspan class=\"small\" title=\"small character: a\">a\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>usque · ad · fanum · \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>L·IULIO·C·F·AGRIPPAE\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>EUERGETAE·\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>HIC·PLATEAM·A·SOSI\u003Cspan class=\"small\" title=\"small character: a\">A\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>USQUE·AD·FANUM·\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of I.Segesta, with the addition of interpunctuation on the basis of photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To Lucius Iulius Agrippa, son of Gaius, euergetes. This man (was responsible for) the street from Sosia all the way to the temple\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The stone is presumably a plaque to be affixed to a statue base, with the word 'hic' referring to the statue of the honorand. Euergetes is the first instance of this Greek word as a calque in Latin. 'a Sosia' presumably refers to a location within the city, and has been suggested to refer to a statue (Dubois), or perhaps a platea or via.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1997.0740 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> 2000.0640 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> 1998.0608 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Nenci 1995 1184 no.11 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001415\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001415\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Michelini 1997 n.12 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001746\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001746\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Nenci 1997 1193 tav.CCXXXV.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001729\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001729\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Paci 2008 333-334 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001687\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001687\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Tribulato 2012 314 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001557\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001557\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ampolo and Erdas 2019 L8 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Slightly irregular letters iwth a broad square module, but narrower towards the end of each line. E has upward curling serifs; triangular interpuncts; final A of line 3 is small, at 29mm.\u003C/p> Line 1-4  52-61  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[284,287,290,293,296,299,302,305],{"id":285,"html":286},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>L(ucio) · Iulio · C(aii) · f(ilio) · Agrippae \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>euergetae · \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>hic · plateam · a · Sosi\u003Cspan class=\"small\" title=\"small character: a\">a\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>usque · ad · fanum · \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>L·IULIO·C·F·AGRIPPAE\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>EUERGETAE·\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>HIC·PLATEAM·A·SOSI\u003Cspan class=\"small\" title=\"small character: a\">A\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>USQUE·AD·FANUM·\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":288,"html":289},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>",{"id":291,"html":292},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of I.Segesta, with the addition of interpunctuation on the basis of photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":294,"html":295},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To Lucius Iulius Agrippa, son of Gaius, euergetes. This man (was responsible for) the street from Sosia all the way to the temple\u003C/p>  ",{"id":297,"html":298},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The stone is presumably a plaque to be affixed to a statue base, with the word 'hic' referring to the statue of the honorand. Euergetes is the first instance of this Greek word as a calque in Latin. 'a Sosia' presumably refers to a location within the city, and has been suggested to refer to a statue (Dubois), or perhaps a platea or via.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":300,"html":301},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1997.0740 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> 2000.0640 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> 1998.0608 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Nenci 1995 1184 no.11 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001415\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001415\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Michelini 1997 n.12 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001746\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001746\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Nenci 1997 1193 tav.CCXXXV.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001729\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001729\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Paci 2008 333-334 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001687\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001687\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Tribulato 2012 314 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001557\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001557\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ampolo and Erdas 2019 L8 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":303,"html":304},"handnote","\u003Cp>Slightly irregular letters iwth a broad square module, but narrower towards the end of each line. E has upward curling serifs; triangular interpuncts; final A of line 3 is small, at 29mm.\u003C/p> Line 1-4  52-61  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":306,"html":307},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[309,311,314,315],{"html":310},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\u003C/a>",{"id":312,"lang":137,"html":313},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>L(ucio) · Iulio · C(aii) · f(ilio) · Agrippae \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>euergetae · \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>hic · plateam · a · Sosi\u003Cspan class=\"small\" title=\"small character: a\">a\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>usque · ad · fanum · \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":310},{"id":316,"lang":137,"html":317},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>L·IULIO·C·F·AGRIPPAE\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>EUERGETAE·\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>HIC·PLATEAM·A·SOSI\u003Cspan class=\"small\" title=\"small character: a\">A\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>USQUE·AD·FANUM·\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[],[320],{"html":63},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Honorific for Lucius Iulius Agrippa, euergetes\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic002737\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">491403\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\">3600028\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002737\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-23\">10.5281/zenodo.4387331\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Segesta\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"site\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/196\">Parco archeologico di Segesta\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">SG2189\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">SG2974\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>A large plaque of limestone made up of three connecting fragments. Intact on all sides.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.limestone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html\">limestone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--ISegesta-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">58.4\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">73.5\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">21.5\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.complete.broken\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Four lines centred on the upper half of the plaque.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Slightly irregular letters iwth a broad square module, but narrower towards the end of each line. E has upward curling serifs; triangular interpuncts; final A of line 3 is small, at 29mm.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line4\">Line 1-4\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"52\" atMost=\"61\">52-61\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"https://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462487\">Segesta\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523171\">Segesta\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.94171, 12.83649\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0014\" notAfter-custom=\"0054\" evidence=\"lettering nomenclature\">Suggested to be Tiberian or Claudian on palaeographic and onomastic grounds\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1992-05\">Found in May 1992, in the fill of the base of the temple on the west side of the agora, in a mediaeval layer\u003Cgeo>37.9396551,12.8418013\u003C/geo>\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- findspot as marked on fig.138 of I.Segesta, located on googlemaps -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.honorific\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html\">honorific\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"draft\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2019-09-23\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag added ISegesta ref\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers\u003C/change>\n\t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-23\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2025-07-04\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag revised from publication\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\u003Csurface/>\u003C!-- \n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic002737_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic002737.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface> -->\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#JP\" source=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>L\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ucio\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> Iulio \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>C\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>aii\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>f\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ilio\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> Agrippae\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>euergetae \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>hic \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> plateam \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> a \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> Sosi\u003Chi rend=\"small\">a\u003C/hi>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>usque \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> ad \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> fanum \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text of I.Segesta, with the addition of interpunctuation on the basis of photograph\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>To Lucius Iulius Agrippa, son of Gaius, euergetes. This man (was responsible for) the street from Sosia all the way to the temple\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>The stone is presumably a plaque to be affixed to a statue base, with the word 'hic' referring to the statue of the honorand. Euergetes is the first instance of this Greek word as a calque in Latin. 'a Sosia' presumably refers to a location within the city, and has been suggested to refer to a statue (Dubois), or perhaps a platea or via.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"AE\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>1997.0740\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/R46KDTZX\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"AE\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>2000.0640\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/R46KDTZX\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"BE\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>1998.0608\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/77P5MNIR\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Nenci\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1995\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>1184 no.11\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/WHBJDH75\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001415\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001415\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Michelini\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1997\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>n.12\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/U7GGTWQM\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001746\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001746\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Nenci\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1997\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>1193 tav.CCXXXV.2\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4FSSHE62\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001729\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001729\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Paci\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2008\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>333-334\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Z54HF9PD\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001687\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001687\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Tribulato\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2012\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>314\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/X5ZZ4GPT\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001557\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001557\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Ampolo and Erdas\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2019\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>L8\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
